HEADWORD: Crankness
<hw>Crank"ness</hw> <pr>(kr?nk"n?s)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>Liability to be overset; -- said of a ship or
other vessel.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Sprightliness; vigor; health.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cranky</ent>⟦br⟧
